WEBVTT

00:00.031 --> 00:02.433
And the problem is fairly simple.

00:02.453 --> 00:04.736
You want to do object detection in images.

00:04.916 --> 00:11.523
Object detection is the task of basically, if I give you an image, you should tell me what is on the image and where.

00:11.863 --> 00:17.428
So in this case, here, you would have to draw me this bounding box and say, this is a deer.

00:18.730 --> 00:21.713
On the bottom, you would have to draw bounding boxes.

00:22.413 --> 00:25.937
Maybe they have to be rectangular, maybe not and say, this is a bus.

00:25.917 --> 00:32.827
And here is a truck and here is another truck and here is a car and so on.

00:33.348 --> 00:36.232
So there can be many objects in an image.

00:36.272 --> 00:37.554
There can be one object.

00:37.594 --> 00:43.302
There can be objects of different classes or there can be no objects at all.

00:43.282 --> 00:53.719
So this is just object detection and there have been many papers on this and specifically there has been this RCNN and this is the model that we're going to extend.

00:53.920 --> 01:00.042
So the RCNN model or specifically the faster RCNN model that we're going to build on

